Hmm, I wouldn't. Basically the thing is, sex is not important. The pleasure sexual brings is temporary, and thus has no value to it. If some experience doesn't remains with you, if it doesn't stands like a tall landmark on the road that is your life, then it's not worth it. Sex exclusively, and things such as alcohol are among these temporary pleasure, that exist just for the sake of forgetting your life for a brief moment of time, and after that back again regretting it. Every experience ought to enrich you in one way or another, and thus no, even if I'm presented with such an opportunity, I wouldn't. A person as an experience, is the best kind of experience. And this best kind of thing is what I value.
